<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="drown-v">drown <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /draʊn/    美 /draʊn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 淹死；(使) 溺死：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a drowning man 
溺水的人</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>淹没；消除 (忧愁等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The streets and houses were drowned by the flood.
街道和房屋被洪水淹没了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Maybe we would soon <strong>be drowned in</strong> the mountain of rubbish.
可能我们很快就要被淹没在堆积成山的垃圾中。</p><footer>2013 广东书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He would <strong>drown his sadness in</strong> coffee. 
他会借咖啡解愁。</p><footer>人教③ – 1</footer></div></div>